Sentencas: Based on commercial solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC), an effective dry reforming catalyst Ni0.7Co0.3/Al2O3+(10% La2O3) was prepared and applied for cell performance test under internal reforming conditions.
Titulo: Application of NixCo1-x catalyst on solid oxide fuel cell anode for biogas dry reforming

Sentencas: The CH4/CO2 ratio of 2:1 corresponds to a power density of 651 mW cm-2 at 850 degrees C, an increase of 384 mW cm-2 compared with the test without catalyst under the same atmosphere.
Titulo: Application of NixCo1-x catalyst on solid oxide fuel cell anode for biogas dry reforming

Sentencas: It is found that catalyst can greatly alleviate the carbon deposition on Ni-based anode when hydrocarbon serves as fuel.
Titulo: Application of NixCo1-x catalyst on solid oxide fuel cell anode for biogas dry reforming

Sentencas: Since CO2 can act as a reforming reactant, no water vapor is required; there is no side-effect of water vapor (diluting the fuel).
Titulo: Application of NixCo1-x catalyst on solid oxide fuel cell anode for biogas dry reforming

Sentencas: This internal DRM technology can help to convert part of the exhaust heat into chemical energy; it is crucial for improving the efficiency of SOFC system fueled with biogas.
Titulo: Application of NixCo1-x catalyst on solid oxide fuel cell anode for biogas dry reforming
